directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Put a 10″ cast iron skillet into the oven – greased with the 1/2 T. canola oil. Allow the pan to heat up while making the cornbread batter.
Sift the Bisquick, cornmeal, sugar, salt, and baking powder in a bowl.
Beat the eggs into the milk, and add to the bowl along with the melted butter. Stir until just combined (do not over-mix).
Pour the batter into the hot skillet.

Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes (or until done and the top is golden brown). You do not have to use a cast iron skillet – a 9″ cake pan will work fine – but I like the golden crust you get when using a heated cast iron skillet.
ingredients: 1/2 T. canola oil (to grease the pan)
title: Hawaiian Cornbread
